President Trump has declared a major disaster in Utah due to severe winter storms and flooding that occurred from February 7 to February 27, 2017. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Nancy M. Casper has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA news desk.